<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747202>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 25. (a–c) Reptolunulites angulosa d’Orbigny; lectotype, MNHN R61485; Late Cretaceous (? Turonian), Sougé, Loir-et-Cher, France; (a) encrusting colony; (b) autozooids and avicularia; (c) early astogeny with ancestrula arrowed. (d–f) Reptolunulites zipfi Taylor and McKinney; holotype, NHMUK BZ 5057; Cretaceous, Campanian, Mount Laurel Formation, Chesapeake and Delaware Canal, New Castle County, Delaware, USA; (d) autozooids, some ovicellate, and avicularia; (b) ovicellate autozooid; (c) avicularium. Scale bars: a = 1 mm; b, f = 200 µm; c, d = 500 µm; e = 100 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4747202/files/figure.png" .

